<!--
  live-theme/templates/index.liquid
  Source of truth for the LIVE theme's (crema-italia-coming-soon-theme,
  id 150557294761) homepage — renders when password protection is OFF.

  Deliberately kept in sync with the main repo's templates/password.liquid
  (the page shown while protection is ON), minus the password-entry box,
  so visitors see the same current design regardless of whether the gate
  is on. See CLAUDE.md §9, 2026-07-07 entry.

  This lives in live-theme/ instead of the main templates/ folder because
  templates/index.liquid in the main tree is the POC4 SPA's homepage — a
  completely different file that must never be pushed to the live theme.

  When the real storefront eventually launches, replace this file's
  content entirely with the production homepage — this is a pre-launch
  stand-in, not the final design.

  Deploy with:
    shopify theme push --theme 150557294761 --path live-theme \
      --only layout/theme.liquid --only templates/index.liquid --allow-live
-->
<section class="ci-section ci-hero">
  <div class="ci-section__inner">
    <div class="ci-hero__logo-wrap">
      <img
        class="ci-hero__logo"
        src="{{ 'ci-logo.png' | asset_url }}"
        alt="Crema Italia"
        width="180"
        height="54"
        loading="eager"
      >
    </div>
    <span class="eyebrow">Italian by Nature</span>
    <h1>Italian coffee, brought over whole.</h1>
    <div class="tricolore-rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <p class="subheading">
      We are selecting a small group of artisan Italian roasters to bring
      their coffee to the U.S. &mdash; origin&#8209;true, never re&#8209;roasted,
      ground, or repackaged by us. If you love all things Italy, a great
      espresso, or the ritual of the Italian bar, you will feel at home here.
      Opening late Summer/Fall 2026.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="ci-section ci-signup">
  <div class="ci-section__inner">
    <div class="founding-banner">
      <strong>Founding Members.</strong> The first 222 subscribers receive
      12% off for life, as active subscribers &mdash; instead of the standard
      10%. The offer closes at 222.
    </div>
    <div class="signup-card" id="signup-card">
      {%- comment -%}
        Shopify's {% form 'customer' %} does a normal server-side POST and
        sets form.posted_successfully? on the way back. The JS in
        assets/crema-italia.js is optional polish on top (typo check,
        double-submit guard, screen-reader announce).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {% form 'customer', id: 'PreLaunchSignup', class: 'signup-form' %}
        {% if form.posted_successfully? %}
          <div class="form-success is-visible" role="status">
            <h3>Grazie.</h3>
            <p>We have your address. We will write when the first pallet lands.</p>
          </div>
        {% else %}
          <h3>Be the first to know.</h3>
          <p class="card-body">
            Sign up now for advance notice of our grand opening &mdash; we
            will write to you once, when the store opens. No noise in
            between.
          </p>

          {{ form.errors | default_errors }}

          <input type="hidden" name="contact[tags]" value="prelaunch-crema-italia, prospect, homepage">

          <div class="form-row">
            <input
              type="email"
              name="contact[email]"
              required
              placeholder="Email address"
              aria-label="Email address"
              autocomplete="email"
            >
            <button type="submit">Notify me</button>
          </div>

          <p class="form-error" role="alert" aria-hidden="true">
            That does not look like a valid email &mdash; try again?
          </p>

          <p class="form-microcopy">
            We use your address only for the pre&#8209;launch announcement.
            Unsubscribe anytime.
          </p>
        {% endif %}
      {% endform %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% render 'ci-footer' %}
